            <q>Employment tribunal procedure regulations may include provision for authorising an employment tribunal &#x2026; (c) to order a representative of a party to proceedings before it to meet all or part of any allowances payable by the Secretary of State under section 5(2)(c) or (3) by reason of the representative's conduct of the proceedings.</q>
            The emphasis here, as I understand it, is conduct of a representative at an employment tribunal. It seems to me that only the tribunal can make an assessment of that representative's conduct and will have to take a decision on that basis. Taking consultation elsewhere
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_97gc' title='Col. 97GC &mdash; HL Deb 14 March 2002 vol 632 c97GC' name='column_97gc' href='#column_97gc' rel='bookmark'>97GC</a>
