      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0632P0-03203'>
        <a name='S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_158'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-doreen-miller' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_158' title='Link to this speech by Ms Doreen Miller' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-doreen-miller" title="Ms Doreen Miller">Baroness Miller of Hendon</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Yes, that is all it is about.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0632P0-03204'>
        <a name='S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_159'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_159' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I know that the noble Baroness is saying that we should stop now. The rule for a Grand Committee is that we should stop at a convenient time between 7.30 p.m. and 8 p.m., not between 7 p.m. and 7.30 p.m. What I proposed, and
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_124gc' title='Col. 124GC &mdash; HL Deb 14 March 2002 vol 632 c124GC' name='column_124gc' href='#column_124gc' rel='bookmark'>124GC</a>
            what happened yesterday, was that we should stop at the conclusion of debate on the amendment which is being debated at 7.30 p.m.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0632P0-03205'>
        <a name='S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_160'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-doreen-miller' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_160' title='Link to this speech by Ms Doreen Miller' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-doreen-miller" title="Ms Doreen Miller">Baroness Miller of Hendon</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I suggest that we get on with Amendment No. 75 therefore, but I certainly intend to speak to our Chief Whip. This is not my understanding at all.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0632P0-03206'>
        <a name='S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_161'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-william-mccarthy' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_161' title='Link to this speech by Mr William McCarthy' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-william-mccarthy" title="Mr William McCarthy">Lord McCarthy</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Is the Minister saying that, in fact, we cannot stop now, because of some rule he has? I think the general wish in the Committee is to stop now. If we go on, many people will go away.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0632P0-03207'>
        <a name='S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_162'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_162' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            The wish of the Government is to make progress on the Bill and we use rules which have been agreed through the usual channels. However, if it is the general wish of the Committee&#x2014;and I do not want to take this as a precedent that we should stop now&#x2014;I beg to move that the proceedings of the Committee should be adjourned until 3.30 p.m. on Monday next.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0632P0-03208'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0632P0_20020314_GCR_163' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The Committee adjourned at twenty-three minutes past seven o'clock.
      </p>
